Neo-McCarthyism is a term used in [[Dazed and Confused (film)|Dazed and Confused]], in a line given from Mike to Pink on the topic of the football coach's decision to implement a contract stating that the signer will not indulge in any illegal activities over the summer.  The term [[McCarthyism]] is in reference to the actions of [[Joseph McCarthy|Senator McCarthy]] in trying to "root out" [[communists]] in the [[United States of America]] during the 1950s.